<LP>
   WAYNE, Pa. -- SEI Corp. said Henry H. Greer was elected
president and chief operating officer.
   Mr. Greer, 52 years old, has been a director of the
company for 12 years, and most recently was executive vice
president in charge of SEI's benefit-services unit and its
information-services division, the company's largest
operation.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   He is a former International Business Machines Corp.
branch manager and a former GTE Corp. marketing executive.
   As SEI's president, he succeeds Alfred P. West Jr., who
remains chairman and chief executive. A company spokesman
said the position of chief operating officer had been vacant
for several years.
