<LP>
   ZURICH -- Switzerland's gross domestic product slowed in
the second quarter, but the economy still grew at a
surprisingly strong rate, according to the Federal Office for
Economic Questions.
   GDP grew at a real annualized rate of 1.6% from the first
quarter, and 3.0% from the 1989 second quarter, the office
said.
