<HL>
   Raet N.V. Acquires
   Computer Service Unit
   Of Switzerland's Adia
</HL>
<DATE>
09/04/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   Z.ADI
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
COMPUTERS AND INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (CPR)
</IN>
<LP>
   ARNHEM, the Netherlands -- Raet NV, a computer software
and services company based here, said it acquired Automation
Center International, known as ACI, from Adia SA of
Switzerland.
   Terms weren't disclosed. Raet said ACI's revenue this year
is expected to total the equivalent of about $70 million,
compared with projected revenue of more than $225 million at
Raet.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Huibert Matthes, chief executive officer of Raet, declined
to disclose profit figures for ACI but said they were better
than the 5.5% return on sales recorded by Raet last year.
   ACI, which has about 500 employees, operates offices in
West Germany, Switzerland, Austria and Belgium. The company's
specialties include setting up computer systems for car
dealers and insurance brokers, as well as operation of data
bases.
   Raet has 1,850 employees. For 1989, the company reported
net profit of 20 million guilders ($11.3 million) on revenue
of 370 million guilders ($209.6 million).
