<HL>
   Canada's Quarterly GDP Fell
</HL>
<DATE>
09/04/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CANDA
</CO>
<LP>
   OTTAWA -- Canada's inflation-adjusted gross domestic
product declined at a compound annual rate of 1.6% in the
second quarter, Statistics Canada, a federal agency, said.
   The downturn affected all major areas of domestic demand,
as well as corporate profits and personal disposable income.
In terms of 1986 prices, GDP was at a seasonally adjusted
annual rate of 571.33 billion Canadian dollars (US$498.09
billion) in the second quarter, off 0.4% from a first-quarter
rate of C$573.69 billion.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The GDP implicit price index rose 0.9% from the first
quarter and 3.1% from a year earlier.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
