   Business Brief -- Gradco Systems Inc.:
   Meeting Reset as Plenum,
   Tash Propose Rival Slate
</HL>
<DATE>
09/04/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   GRCO PLEN
</CO>
<IN>
OFFICE EQUIPMENT (OFF)
</IN>
<LP>
   Gradco Systems Inc. adjourned its annual meeting last
Friday after 8.9%-holder Plenum Publishing Corp. and its
chairman Martin Tash said they would seek to elect their own
slate of directors.
   Plenum disclosed its plans in a filing with the Securities
and Exchange Commission earlier last week. Gradco, an Irving,
Calif., maker of paper-handling equipment, responded by
adjourning the meeting until Oct. 12 to give the company time
to mail additional proxy materials regarding Plenum's recent
actions to shareholders.
