<HL>
   Marketing Brief -- First Ameri-Cable Corp.:
   Most Assets Sold to TCI;
   Holders to Receive Proceeds
</HL>
<DATE>
09/04/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   FATV
</CO>
<IN>
MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
DIVIDENDS (DIV)
</IN>
<LP>
   First Ameri-Cable Corp., a cable television company based
in Columbus, Ohio, said that it sold substantially all of its
assets to TCI Holdings Inc., a Denver-based cable TV concern,
for about $40 million, and that it will distribute net
proceeds to shareholders.
   The company said it intends to distribute on about Sept.
17 at least 15 cents a share to stock of record Sept. 11.
First Ameri-Cable has about 54 million shares outstanding.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   An additional distribution of as much as three cents a
share will be made in March 1992, the company said. That
payment will be made from an escrow fund of $1.6 million that
the company established to provide for certain post-closing
obligations and any breaches of contractual representations
or warranties.
</TEXT>
