TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Standard Products Co., Cleveland, said it bought the
Plastic/Magnetic Products division of Pantasote Inc.,
Greenwich, Conn. Terms weren't disclosed.
   The unit makes extruded and molded plastic and magnetic
parts for home appliances and other uses. Sales last year
were $24 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Standard Products, which is mainly a producer of rubber
and plastic parts for cars and trucks, in 1989 bought Holm
Industries, a maker of plastic and magnetic door seals for
home appliances and residential doors. The newly acquired
unit will complement the Holm operations, Standard Products
said.
